The paper deals with the problem of recovering a complete matrix from sparse data, which is a central problem in dictionary learning and has applications in signal processing and machine learning. This problem is related to compressed sensing and optimization, which are topics covered in several CS sub-categories. Specifically, the paper uses nonconvex optimization and geometric analysis to develop an efficient algorithm for matrix recovery, which suggests that it may belong to sub-categories such as cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
